A leading U.S. Banker said the dollarwas likely to fall another five to 10 pct this year and animprovement in the huge American trade deficit would be onlytemporary at current world exchange rate levels.    Kurt Viermetz, worldwide treasurer of Morgan Guaranty TrustCo, told Arab currency traders meeting here that the steadydepreciation of the dollar had not gone far enough to rein inU.S. deficits on a lasting basis. Reuter&#3;